<!ENTITY foobar.ops.tabsdesc1 "When performing a search, Foobar will open the results either in the current tab or in a new tab, depending.">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.tabsdesc2 "If 'Always open search results in the current tab' is selected, then, obviously, the current tab will always be used.">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.tabsdesc3 "If, however, 'Open search results in a new tab, if needed' is selected, a new tab will not always be opened.  The">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.tabsdesc4 "current tab will still be used if it is set to a blank document.  This way you can open a new tab for your search">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.tabsdesc5 "without worrying about it going to waste.">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.tabsdesc6 "When searching with multiple search engines, this setting only applies to the results from the first engine given.">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.tabsdesc7 "The results from all the remaining engines will open in new tabs.">

