<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc1 "In addition to setting a default search engine via the location bar's new search icon, you can also select what">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc2 "engine(s) you'd like to use on a per-search basis!">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc3 "Example:  /g/wiki foobar">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc4 "The syntax used here is this:  the desired engines separated by the delimiting character (a slash by default),">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc5 "followed by a space and then your search string.">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc6 "The engines are matched in one of two ways:  by keyword or by name.  You can designate keywords under">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc7 "'Manage search engines...' in the search icon's menu; or, if you choose to go by engine name, then all you">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc8 "must do is spell each name out far enough to match the desired engine.">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.delimitdesc9 "Note:  keywords should not contain the delimiter character.">

<!ENTITY foobar.ops.ctrlscroll "Must hold ctrl key when scrolling engines">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.ctrlscroll1 "Default behavior for the search bar, which has been duplicated for Foobar, allows you to change the current">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.ctrlscroll2 "search engine without clicking the search icon.  When the focus is on the bar, you can hold the control key">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.ctrlscroll3 "and press up or down to change engines.  You can also hold the mouse over the bar, hold the control key, and">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.ctrlscroll4 "use the scroll wheel to do the same thing.  Deselecting this option allows you to use the scroll wheel in the">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.ctrlscroll5 "same manner without the need to hold the control key; however, the control key will still be necessary when">
<!ENTITY foobar.ops.ctrlscroll6 "changing engines via the up and down arrows.">